Alex Ferguson, the multiple trophy-winning former manager of Manchester United, and now an LMA committee member, paid tribute to Guardiola by saying: "As well as being a truly gifted manager and leader, you always display admirable humility and composure and I am sure your family must be very proud of you."Guardiola's award came just days after it was announced that City defender Ruben Dias had been voted the footballer of the year by England's Football Writers Association. Â 